name: YMCA GOOD SHEPHERD WRAP AROUND EHS
PENNYS CHILD CARE CENTER LLC
details:
At Penny's Child Care Center, LLC we strive to provide a safe, loving, and stimulating environment for all of the children in our care, ages 6 weeks through 8 years. 
 
We believe in fulfilling each child's basic needs: love, trust, security, positive self-image, health, and safety.  Our staff is committed to the development of each 8child as an individual and will both encourage and assist him/her to become a well-adjusted, happy, and independent person.
 
At Penny's Child Care Center, we provide the children with breakfast, lunch, and snacks, prepared onsite daily.
 
With our preschool program, we've successfully assisted in preparing hundreds of children to flourish in their formal education throughout Janesville, Milton, Edgerton, and surrounding school districts.

name: CENTRAL LUTHERAN PRESCHOOL & 4K
details: In our preschool and 4K classes we believe that the basis for learning in young children is their active play. Our programs nurture and support the individual and unique development of young children by emphasizing developmentally appropriate activities that address each child's need for and interest in creativity, language skills, problem solving and decision making skills, cognitive growth, social interaction, physical movement, family involvement, and fun.

name: Preschool & Daycare at Central Christian Church
details: We are a State Licensed Christian Preschool and Daycare offering Preschool part day sessions for 2–5 year olds and Daycare for 6 weeks–8 year olds. Our staff are highly qualified, loving, and experienced individuals. Our fresh and fun facility is a great place for children to grow, create, explore and learn. We are fortunate to have a state of the art children’s facility. As well as being safe, fun and inviting, it is also the perfect space to house all of our different play and learning areas. These areas include:  Blocks and Building, Dramatic Play, Puzzles, Science, Sensory, Wood Working, Music, Math, Manipulatives, Writing, and Library. Included are many fun and high quality learning materials for each child to choose from. There is plenty of space for Creative Art, Community Circle Time, Group Music, and Cooking Projects. Our curriculum consists of learning activities that teach a variety of skills. Areas of learning include: Math, Language, Phonetics,Art, Music, Science, Social Play, Physical Play, Practicing Independent Skills, and Developing Christian Characteristics. All activities are fun, age appropriate, and hands on. Daily routines allow for both teacher directed and child directed exploring and learning. Snacks are provided daily.

name: CREATIVE ARTS CLASS LLC
details: Creative Arts Class , LLC offers a hands on, developmentally appropriate program that builds the social, emotional, physical, and intellectual development of our children through well-planned activities that encourage self-discovery.

name: YWCA VAN BUREN CHILD CARE PROGRAM
OUR LADY OF ASSUMPTION CCC
details:
OLA Childcare has served parish families and the community since 1997, providing innovative, quality childcare and education centered on Catholic values. Our goal is to help each child develop emotionally, intellectually, socially and physically by providing experiences that encourage:

Self Esteem
Awareness of others’ needs and recognition of efforts
Self-expression and communication skills
Intellectual growth
Social interaction
Large and small muscle development
Prayer and awareness of the gospel message
No childcare operation can replace your presence. However,  OLA Childcare Center acts as an extension of your home environment, reflecting your values when we care for and educate your children.

We are happy you have taken the time to consider us for your child care needs.  Please take a moment to familiarize yourself with our fees, policies and center!

name: ST JOHNS LITTLE SAINTS LEARNING CTR
LADYSMITH HEAD START
details: Head Start is a comprehensive child development program that serves children from low-income families, ages 3-5, including children with disabilites. However, over-income families may be eligible for the program depending upon other needs within the family. Children who attend Head Start participate in a variety of educational activities designed to foster learning, and social/emotional and physical development. The classrooms are equipped for "hands on" learning and teachers follow an age appropriate curriculum. Nutrition and health are also an important part of the Head Start experience. Head Start offers your child an opportunity to develop social, physical, and readiness skills necessary for a successful kindergarten experience. Nutrition, health and safety activities are also included in the daily curriculum resulting in children enjoying healthy meals as well as being aware of their personal health and safety.

name: MY PLACE ON MAIN LLC
details:
My Place Children and Family Center aims to provide a developmentally appropriate environment where any and every child feels a sense of belonging.  A place where they can grow strong and healthy physically, cognitively, emotionally and socially.

We offer full service licensed child care for ages 6 weeks to 12 years.  In addition, we offer a comprehensive preschool program for children ages 3 to 5 years to promote early learning and the building of a firm academic foundation.

name: CHILDRENS DAY CENTER & PRESCHOOL
details: Our goal at Children’s Day Center is to provide a nurturing, safe and stimulating environment that embraces learning through play to promote the physical, social, emotional and cognitive development of our students.  We believe children learn best by “doing,” and encourage creativity, curiosity and exploration. Given opportunities to explore the world around them, young children become active, involved learners. Children’s Day Center is a place where they can be successful and discover that learning is fun. We believe that it takes a village to raise a child, and the child care provider is part of a family’s village. Parent involvement is encouraged at Children’s Day Center. Together with parents, we foster a community of support by having open and regular communication between teachers and parents. We hope to build this support system through monthly parent meetings, family events and volunteer opportunities.

Parents love Kids Klub because it is a safe, affordable place their kids enjoy that is open anytime school is not -- that includes snow days, vacation days and a summer program filled with fun 7:00 AM - 6:00 PM.  We are licensed by the State of Wisconsin and have trained staff to work with kids.

details: At Under The Rainbow Child Care of Shawano, WI, we understand the importance of finding child care professionals who will nurture, educate, and look after your child. That’s why our teachers are dedicated to fostering an environment in which your child will learn gleefully.

details:
The Tender Loving Christian Child Care Center, an early childhood ministry of Trinity Lutheran Church-Town Wilson, advances the kingdom of our Lord as we let the little children come to Jesus and care for them.

In this warm and loving Christian-centered environment, congregation members, staff and the family work together helping each child in their total development. Each child is allowed to develop to their fullest potential spiritually, socially, physically, creatively, intellectually and emotionally. Within this environment and thorough planned activities, each child builds on the foundation of Christ for their future success.

name: LITTLE SHEPHERDS INN
details:
LITTLE SHEPHERDS INN is a state licensed child care center for six weeks through 12 year old children.  We extend an invitation to tour our facilities at your convenience.  Stop in any time or call to set up an appointment (668-6261).

In addition to the School Readiness Program, we offer full time, part time, before and after school, school age summer adventure program and drop in care.  We are open Monday through Friday 6:00am to 6:00pm.

LITTLE SHEPHERDS INN is staffed with experienced care professionals who are licensed in their fields—a Wisconsin Certified Early Childhood (BA Degree) Teacher and Child Development (Associate Degree) Teachers on staff.

name: SALVATION ARMY DAY CARE CENTER
details: Now located at 1125 North 13th Street in Sheboygan, our day care serves children 6 weeks to 12 years old.  The facility has an infant room, a toddler room, two preschool rooms, and a school-age room. Each room has an adjoining rest room. Nutritious meals and snacks are provided. The facility houses a fully stocked in-house library. Two separate outdoor play areas with various outdoor play equipment cater to the different age groups along with an indoor gross motor area.

name: YMCA FALLS LITTLE FRIENDS
details: As parents we realize you have a great deal to juggle. Finding quality child care you can trust shouldn’t be part of it.  The Sheboygan County YMCA Child Care program uses the Wisconsin Model Early Learning Standards through theme based curriculum and is a part of the Young Stars Program.  Our goal is to provide a warm, relaxed, home-like atmosphere in which the children can grow and develop.  We also help children reach their fullest potential by: developing self-awareness, confidence and feelings of self worth, develop interpersonal relationships, values development, emergent learning, develop physical skills and focus on health and fitness.

name: UMOS PLYMOUTH MHS DAY CARE CENTER
YMCA CAMP ST CROIX
details: YMCA Camp St. Croix has been providing exceptional outdoor program experiences since 1909. For more than 100 years, Camp St. Croix has established a tradition of youth development, healthy living, and social responsibility in all of our year-round programs. Just 20 minutes east of the Twin Cities, St. Croix provides a convenient location for kids and adults alike to enjoy quality programming in a beautiful, natural setting.

name: YMCA CAMP ST CROIX - RIVER CREST
details:
YMCA Camp St. Croix provides Before & After Care and School Release Day Care for children who attend River Crest Elementary School. For your convenience, the program is located at River Crest Elementary School (note: some release days may be held at Camp St. Croix).

Safety is our top priority. Parents/guardians sign their children in to the program in the morning and students walk to class when school starts. In the afternoon, students walk from class to the School Age Care Program and parents/guardians must sign children out at pick up time. A portion of the program may be spent at YMCA Camp St Croix located directly across from the school. Children are escorted by staff through the tunnel connecting the two locations.
business hours:
Before School Care: 6:00 a.m. – 9:00 a.m.
After School Care: 3:45 p.m. – 6:00 p.m.

name: FOUR SEASONS CHILD CARE INC
details:
Mission Statement:
The entire staff of Four Seasons Child Care is committed to providing a unique caring environment, which embraces the physical, emotional, social, and cognitive strengths and needs of each individual child.

Philosophy:
The entire staff of Four Seasons Child Care is dedicated to providing a nurturing, safe, and stimulating environment that allows children of all ages to reach their full potential through interactive learning. We believe children should be treated with sincere respect and kindness. All children are given opportunities to explore materials and participate in a variety of unique experiences. Activities are carefully planned and implemented in a child-centered setting. Numerous age-appropriate activities including art, music, multi-language development, science, math, nature, and dramatic play are offered to every child. Children will develop self-esteem, independence, and problem-solving skills within a secure and predictable environment under the loving leadership of trusted staff.

name: LITTLE ADVENTURES CHILD CARE CTR
details:
Little Adventures will provide a loving and caring environment that teaches children the values and responsibilities of everyday life. The philosophy of the center is to help each child grow in his or her own individual way, while remaining focused on the unique strengths and abilities that every child brings to our world. We also feel it is important for children to have many experiences that will help lead them to a better understanding of the world around them so that they can embrace it with arms wide open. Our goal is to strive to maintain this philosophy while giving parents the peace of mind that their child is being well cared for in a consistently safe and dependable environment.

Little Adventures will be developmentally appropriate in all aspects to assure that young minds are learning new things and important life skills each and every day through a combination of play and carefully planned educational techniques.

name: DAISY HILL
details: We believe that all children have a right to a safe, nurturing environment where they feel comfortable and secure. We believe that children have a right to develop to their maximum ability and that our staff, together with a child's parents can work together to create environments that will promote a child's physical, cognitive and social emotional growth. We recognize that each child is an individual and we respect each child's social, developmental and physical differences. We believe that every child has the right to a strong positive self-image and to feel good about whom they are. We hope that in working in a partnership with a child's family, and in treating each child with love and respect, that they in return will learn to treat others with the same respect. We believe that children learn best through active participation with and in their environment and it is our job to provide a variety of opportunities and experiences to promote growth in all areas of child development. We strive to thoughtfully plan activities that meet the developmental needs of all children and that will enhance a child's life preparing them for a successful journey toward a lifetime of learning.

details:
Bethel Little Lamb Preschool exists for the purpose of aiding and assisting parents in their God-given role to "...bring your children up in the training and instruction of the Lord." (Ephesians 6:4). 

Our preschool is dedicated to the purpose of preserving and strengthening  the Christian Church so that the Gospel of Jesus Christ will be spread effectively from generation to generation.
Children attending Little Lamb Preschool hear the truths of God's Word, the Bible.
 
They also are offered a variety of activities that work to develop the whole child:
- spiritually
- intellectually
- physically
- socially
- emotionally
- creatively

Our program reflects the developmental level of each child through active and quiet, individual and group, and indoor and outdoor activities.  We believe in providing a program that offers a nurturing environment with varied educational experiences.

name: WESTBY DAY CARE & LEARNING CTR INC
LITTLE PINE CONES LODGE CDC LLC
EAGLE RIVER HEAD START
details:
The Northland Pines Early Childhood Program uses a collaborative approach to teaching children, ages 3-5 years old, who have been identified as having significant delay(s)s in their development. The goal is to provide children with early intervention services, through individual and small group instruction, in their least restrictive environment. Services may include, but are not limited to direct instruction, speech therapy, occupational therapy, and physical therapy. Placement options are based upon individual needs, require an initial evaluation to determine eligibility, and may include one of the following:

1.     Traditional Early Childhood Programming
2.     Collaborative Early Childhood Programming with Community-based Program
3.     Collaborative Early Childhood Programming with 4K.
4.     Collaborative Early Childhood Programming with 5K
5.     Itinerant services

We encourage families, service providers, and preschool and day care providers to contact the school district if there is a concern about a child’s development. We offer FREE developmental screenings which are used to assess progress toward developmental milestones, provide parents with awareness of child growth, and effectively communicate development concerns.

name: TERRIS TREEHOUSE
details:
Our goal to all children in our area is to set higher expectations and continue to raise the bar for Early Childhood Education.  Our Program offers a nurturing play-based learning environment that is developmentally appropriate.  We implement a multitude of learning opportunities, which promote advancement in growth, confidence and explorations in all the aspects of individual development; sociably, cognitively, physical, emotionally.  These Objectives helps certain skills emerge such abilities to; prepare themselves confidently for school, work cooperatively, form healthy relationships, maintain self-esteem, resiliency, making and recognizing positive choices, and feed their inner imagination of the world around them.

Our teachers are all educated and well qualified.  They continually further their education to confidently support progression in all the dimensions of development, while gaining new innovative teaching techniques.  With serving each child’s particular needs and individuality, we provide encouragement and direction as we continuously provoke intellectual engagement.  Our teaching techniques are practiced through guidance, which helps each child discover and want to learn on their own.  We know as teachers that consistency, communication, trust, patience, modeling and motivating help children learn.  These accomplishments help them immensely in being prepared for future circumstances in life. 

Our environment objective is to create a curriculum and atmosphere that provokes both their natural wonder and senses.  Children become familiar with such real life elements and learn through cause and effect, interacting socially through play and structured activities while shaping and discovering their identity, and unique talents.  We offer a positive, safe, creative, and nurturing environment for that wonderful window of opportunity in their early childhood development.

name: CAMP JORN YMCA CHILD CARE CENTER
details:
Located on the Camp Jorn YMCA property, we offer a full day, year round quality child care program using a play-based curriculum which allows each child to grow at their own pace in the areas of social, emotional, physical and academic development. Warm, caring, educated staff provide care in a casual, relaxed setting where the needs and interests of both child and parent are recognized.

Summer child care available by the day, week or month.  Must be preregistered.  No drop-ins.  Call or email for more information.

name: LITTLE ACORNS LODGE CHILD DC LLC
details:
Our Center
Little Acorns Lodge is located in the unique northwoods setting of Saint Germain, 1 block from north of the corner of HWY 70 & HWY 155

 Our Curriculum
Our approach is simple: To provide your child with a nurturing safe environment filled with encouragement. The goal of our early childhood curriculum is to help children become enthusiastic learners. We nurture a lifelong love of learning in your child. Our curriculum fosters the growth & development of the whole child in areas of: Social, Emotional, Physical, Creative and Cognitive

 Our Philosophy
We believe that the early childhood years are the most important learning years. Each child is UNIQUE. Young children learn best in a child centered, creative play environment. Caring, nurturing & supportive teachers, educated & experienced in early childhood education, facilitate your childs progression of knowledge & development competence.

name: UNITED CHILD CARE CENTER
details: Serving children and their families since 1995, United Child Care Center is a non-profit child care and preschool. We care for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years, and also operate a before and after school program with bus service to Central-Denison Elementary, Eastview Elementary, and St. Francis Catholic School. Our goal lies in education of the whole child by providing learning opportunities for cognitive, physical, and social-emotional growth. Our mission is to provide quality early childhood care and education in a safe and nurturing environment. We strive to strengthen the bridge between work and family life by creating a special place that supports them both.

name: LAKELAND'S LTL LEARNERS-TIBBETS
details:
LLL provides a warm and caring atmosphere for children when they are away from home. Our philosophy is that every child shall be cared for, nurtured, and guided as is needed for that child to grow physically, mentally, and emotionally. The children’s basic needs shall be cared for with TLC and the curriculum shall be presented through the philosophy of learning through play. Rooms are set up with learning centers so that children are able to learn and experiment at their own pace.  Children are allowed to choose activities that interest them and move from center to center as their interests dictate or lead them.

 We believe that it is vital that young children have a rich and nurturing environment in which to spend their days. Our vision to accomplish this:
- A facility that offers warm, safe and engaging areas with adequate space.
- Materials that will stimulate the child's play and development.
- Curriculum that will enrich the child's day and help them to achieve their full potential.
- Quality teachers that are educated and compensated so they can continue to give their best to the children and families they serve.

MISSION STATEMENT

Center is to offer Christ as the central focus in the
life of every child, so that every facet of their day
relates to Christ and His purpose for them.
We seek to provide for their physical, social, emo-

name: DELAVAN NURSERY CENTER
details:
In response to a growing need in the community, the Delavan Nursery Center will now be open from 7:00 am to 5:00 pm. name: AFTER SCHOOL - MAGEE
details:
Magee is a preschool through 5th grade-elementary school, of just under 300 students, that sits on 21 acres in western Waukesha County, Wisconsin. The campus includes a butterfly garden, wooded area and remnant prairie that serve as outdoor classrooms for our students. Remnants of the original Magee schoolhouse embellish the front foyer to remind all who enter of our rich history. Magee staff honors the principle of old-fashioned school values as we invite parents and community members to visit and engage in children's day-to-day learning. The importance of teaching the whole child is evident in Magee's Mission and Belief Statements. "The mission of the Magee Community is to inspire students to "Think, Reflect, Achieve, Create and be Kind."

At Magee, the positive learning environment works in tandem with strong academic rigor to produce excellence in our students. Their academic performance includes consistently earning some of the state's highest scores on standardized tests. The innovative use of technology through personalized learning opportunities challenges students to advance as readers, writers, problem solvers and thinkers.

The dedicated staff all work together to make Magee worthy of Blue Ribbon status. There is a high level of collegiality among the staff that includes all adults in the building from support staff to classroom teachers to specialists to the principal. Students are the beneficiaries of this common purpose and shared respect, for all in the building are striving for the same purpose. Our purpose is our kids!

details: Cushing Elementary is home to 458 4K through fifth grade students. Located in the community of Delafield our school is proud of the variety of opportunities we provide for students within and outside of the school day. Our mission is to provide a strong, educational foundation for all children by promoting an excitement for learning through challenging experiences in a safe, flexible, positive environment. We value our partnership with family, staff, and community. Our school has a highly qualified teaching staff that believes strongly in the power of professional learning communities and professional growth to promote student achievement.

name: AFTER SCHOOL - SUMMIT VIEW
details:
Welcome to Summit View Elementary School! It is one of 15 elementary schools in the School District of Waukesha. Summit View opened in the fall of 1992. It is a large elementary school that strives to know and enhance each child's unique qualities.

Summit View's physical structure offers students the best of all educational settings. Input into the design of the building was sought from educators, students, parents, and business leaders. There are seven teaching pods which house approximately 650 students in grades kindergarten through fifth. Within each pod there are opportunities for individual as well as small and large group instruction. A teacher planning area, surrounded by a computer area, opens out into four classrooms in each of the pods in grades. Movable walls offer teachers opportunities to vary the learning environment. There are computers located in classrooms, on movable carts, the lab, and in the media center. Other technologies available to students and staff include data projectors, visual presenters, smart boards, Elmo projectors, and digital cameras.

The staff at Summit View embraces a variety of teaching strategies and philosophies. Best practices such as Reader's and Writer's workshop are utilized. Using the district Response to Intervention (R.T.I.) model, interventions occur to provide additional support to students. Students are encouraged to develop independence, be creative and critical thinkers, appreciate and respect individual differences, and become effective problem solvers. We want all of our students to become life-long learners.

Using a Professional Learning Community model, Summit View's staff collaborates to share ideas, analyze data, and plan lessons to help all students succeed. Open communication between home and school is vital. Parent input is one of the keys to the success of students.

We are proud of Summit View and the children who attend it. If you ever have any questions, please feel free to contact the principal, Mr. Peterson.

name: PILGRIM LUTHERAN PRESCHOOL & CC
details: Pilgrim isn’t just a school or a church, but a group of people who thrive on community and relationships. Here, the school faculty knows each of their student’s parents by first name, teachers and parents work side by side to ensure student success, and students treat each other with respect and Christian love. Here, members are like family who celebrate together and support each other in times of need. Here, children and adults alike cultivate friendships that last a lifetime.

details:
Little Lambs Christian Childcare and Preschool is a ministry of  Good Shepherd United Methodist Church. We are located in the downtown area of Oconomowoc, Wisconsin.  We have provided quality child care and preschool for over 25 years.  Our objective is to provide a developmentally appropriate curriculum to enhance development in the areas of social interaction, large, and small motor, language, self-help, and cognitive skills in a Christian environment.

We are licensed and regulated by the State of Wisconsin’s Department of Children and Family Services. We provide child care and preschool services to children between the ages of 6 weeks and 12 years old.

We are open year round Monday through Friday from 6:00am to 6:00pm, excluding major holidays.

name: ALL ABOUT LEARNING - SILVER SPRING
details:
All About Learning was founded in 1991 by its owners, Corinne Thiesen and Tracy Aslin.

Corinne graduated from UW- Stout with a degree in Child Development and Family Life. Tracy graduated from UWMadison with a degree in Early Childhood Education. Corinne and Tracy’s desire to own and operate a child care center that would provide high-quality, educational care for children, was developed while working together for other child care providers.

The first All About Learning, located in West Allis, was opened in 1991. It is still in operation today. In 1993, we opened our second center in Oconomowoc. Our third location opened in 1997 in Waukesha. Our fourth location is in Menomonee Falls, located right on Silver Spring. This center opened in the summer of 2000. We opened our Hartland center in October of 2000. In September 2003 we opened our 6th location on Main Street in Menomonee Falls. In June of 2005 we moved our West Allis center to a new location which is on 106th and Lincoln. In summer of 2007 we opened a brand new facility in Oconomowoc, which offers a huge indoor gym, Birthday party and training room. This new building also offers a high tech Hepa filter and UV system designed to collect 99.9% of airborne particles and allergens including dust mites, bacteria and attached viruses. In addition to this, we have installed in house video monitors and recorder in all classrooms for observation and training.

As we are growing, we are continually finding that the need for quality childcare centers is expansive. All About Learning is a growing company dedicated to maintaining quality. We are consistently looking for ways to improve our services through new technology, higher education, and individualized care. Through the growth of this company we have learned to improve our facilities to better meet the needs of the children, families, staff and community. All of our centers operate under the strict guidelines of the National Accreditation Credentials (NAC) program requirements. To learn more about the Accreditation process and requirements visit the NAC website at: www.naccp.org

All About Learning respects the parent’s/guardian’s role and influence in the care of their child/ren. We appreciate any input and information that you can share with us regarding your child and your expectations.

name: NEW LONDON HEAD START
address: 709 W PINE ST / UNIT METH CH
details:
Head Start began in 1965 as part of President Lyndon Johnson’s “War on Poverty”. Federally funded by the United States Department of Health and Human Services, this early childhood program for income eligible and special needs pre-school children and their families provides comprehensive services in the areas of early childhood education, health, and family and community partnerships. Both center-based and home-based options are available.

Parents are a child’s first teacher and have the longest lasting influence on their lives; therefore, parent involvement is a vital part of the program. Families with children ages three to five are encouraged to apply anytime throughout the year. Families whose children have special needs are also encouraged to apply.

Research shows that Head Start produces long term benefits and significant cost savings by reducing grade retentions, school dropouts, delinquency, substance abuse, and referrals to special education.

CAP Services provides Head Start services in Marquette, Portage, Waupaca, and Waushara counties.

details: St. Paul’s Lutheran Child Center is a group childcare center-serving all children from 6 weeks to 12 years old. We offer morning and afternoon pre-school programs, all day childcare and an after school program. St. Paul’s Child Care serves by nurturing the faith of children in their dear Savior, and demonstrating practical ways to live their faith in Christ. Along with Christian values, Bible lessons and prayers, to help a child grow spiritually, St. Paul’s Child Care provides activities to help each child grow and develop socially, emotionally, physically, and intellectually. Children will have the opportunity to partake in self initiated or teacher directed activities. Group activities along with individual activities will also be provided. At St. Paul’s Child Center, we believe children learn through play and not all children learn the same way. Children need to have age appropriate activities presented and taught in a variety of different ways to help each child strive to succeed to the best of their ability.

details: The Biron Center is fortunate to offer a variety of program options. We have three Infant/Toddler classrooms that run year round, Monday thru Friday from 7:30am-4:15pm. name: WASHINGTON PRYME TIME AFTER SCH PRO
details:
Parents - are you rushing to school during work hours to pick up your children or are they going home to an empty house? Pryme Time After School Care is your affordable and convenient answer and there is no need to be a Y member to participate in this program.

The Y's After School Care program is a state-licensed childcare program offered to all K-6th grade students enrolled in Grant, Lincoln, Nasonville, Washington or Stratford (Zion Lutheran Church) elementary schools. Children will receive a healthy snack, homework assistance, and guidance from Y staff trained and certified in group activities and socialization skills. The program begins the first day of school and runs according to the school calendar. Hours are immediately after school until 6:00 pm.

name: Cumberland School District
details: Cumberland Elementary is fortunate to have highly qualified professional and dedicated staff members who are truly committed to providing your child with the best education in a caring environment. Our students take pride in being respectful, responsible, cooperative, and they love coming to school at Cumberland Elementary!  Please feel free to come visit and observe first hand the warm, caring, academically challenging, and student- centered school that has been created through a partnership among, staff, parents, students, and community members. We are thrilled to have Cumberland Elementary be your school of choice.

name: MAPLE TREE EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
details: “Strong Roots Produce Strong Minds” is our motto.  Maple Tree School is committed to the goal of working to ensure that every student is proficient or advanced in reading and writing across all content areas.  Our school promotes an educational environment that aligns curriculum and instruction to the Common Core State Standards.  At Maple Tree, we educate all students for success in higher education, careers, and responsible citizenship.  Our school offers Child Care- Ages 2-3, a Head Start – Early Childhood Program, and grades K4 – 5th.  Maple Tree School has smaller class sizes with our Student Achievement Guarantee in Education (SAGE) program for grades K5 – 3rd. Our West Side Y and Downtown Y locations provide full-day programming, from 6:30 am to 6:00 pm, on all official "no school" days. name: FAMILY FORUM HEAD START CENTER #10
details:
Head Start is a federally-funded comprehensive, quality preschool program that provides learning experiences focusing on the domains of learning.  Head Start assists in the development of social competence so preschoolers will be ready for and successful in school.

Family Forum, Inc. provides Head Start services and works in partnership with families to provide a strong support network for low-income families of preschool children.  Head Start provides preschool children and their families with activities that help them grow cognitively, socially, emotionally, and physically.  Head Start helps all children and their families succeed.

Services are offered to meet the special needs of children with disabilities.  The Head Start staff recognize that, as parents, you are the first and most important teachers of your children.  We welcome your involvement in Head Start activities and will work as partners with you to help your child and family progress.  If you or a family member has a special concern, you can receive help though Head Start.  Head Start staff work with and support families in need of medical, nutritional, social, educational, and employment services through identifying and utilizing community resources.  We will also follow up to ensure you receive the assistance needed.

name: Ymca Of Dane Co. Winnequah
details:
Foster Cognitive, Physical and Social Development We offer the best child care with a strong curriculum based on the YMCA four core values: Caring, Honesty, Respect and Responsibility.

​With so many demands on today's families and the increased focus on early childhood development, families need all the support they can get to nurture the potential of youth. We support children by providing a safe and healthy place to learn foundational skills, develop healthy, trusting relationships and build self-reliance through the Y values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility.

At the Y, we believe the values and skills learned early on are vital building blocks for quality of life and future success. That's why our child care programs are staffed with people who understand the cognitive, physical and social development of kids, the need children have to feel connected and supported in trying new things, and the caring and reinforcement parents and families need to help each other.

Willows provides a Christian enriched curriculum through meal prayers and bible stories. We are not affiliated with any church or Christian denomination.

Willows participates in the Department of Public Instruction’s food program serving breakfast, lunch and afternoon snack as part of you fees. Any allergies your child has will be respected.

Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. name: Maple Leaf Academy
details:
Maple Leaf Academy Preschool of the North Shore offers a professionally designed, Montessori philosophy curriculum; complete with lesson plans, progress reports, writing journals and newsletters for parents to use as a guide. Children learn through hands on play and structured activities in our well organized classrooms.  We strive to keep a positive and nurturing atmosphere in the classroom.  We continuously work on social development, emphasizing respect, kindness and getting along with others.  We use "teachable moments" as opportunities to reinforce the children's academic and social skills.  Our classrooms are organized into "learning environments."   These are areas where the children can find toys and materials related by theme, interest, and skills. details:
Welcome to the vibrant, nurturing learning community of Lloyd Barbee MPS Montessori. Our school offers a high quality education, dedicated teaching staff and unique learning opportunities to our students, families and community. The MPS Citywide Montessori Council, a leadership group of Montessori teachers and administrators, led this great initiative from the beginning, and the council will continue to support its successful organization.

The Montessori method of education is based on the philosophy that children reach their fullest potential through multi-age interactions in an inquiring, cooperative and encouraging atmosphere. Our staff focuses on fostering competent and responsible students who demonstrate creativity, concentration, coordination and independence in their work. The Montessori environment and teachers ensure that our young learners build confidence in their abilities, feel good about their school experience and develop peaceful relationships with their peers.

Dr. Maria Montessori believed that the work of education is shared between the student, teacher and environment. The curriculum and learning that takes place at Lloyd Barbee Montessori is not the typical teacher to student interaction. Teachers collaborate with children while they learn, creating a communal environment. Students participate in interactive, hands-on learning that leads to high self-esteem and a deep-rooted love for learning. When you observe a Montessori classroom, you will see learning taking place in its purest form – a truly beautiful thing to watch!

Parents and families are central stakeholders at Lloyd Barbee  Montessori School and there are a multitude of opportunities for parent participation that keeps families involved in their child’s education. Young children rely on a strong support system as they develop into confident, responsible elementary scholars. With a variety of events taking place within the school environment throughout the year, families have the opportunity to experience the Lloyd Barbee MPS Montessori atmosphere firsthand and to build a strong connection to their school community.

We also partner with DentaQuest, Uniting Garden Homes and Common Ground.

name: TREVOR-WILMOT KIDS CLUB
details:
In the spring of 2005, the Trevor school board began consolidation discussions with the neighboring Wilmot Grade School District. Both school boards then passed a resolution that called for a referendum to be placed on the November 2005 ballot to ask the community if they favored consolidation. Over 70% of the voters in Trevor and over 70% of the voters in Wilmot voted for the consolidation. The final Trevor total showed 194 "Yes" votes and 78 "No" ballots and Wilmot results were 148 "Yes" and 51 "No." Wisconsin's newest school district, the Trevor-Wilmot Consolidated School District was created on July 1, 2006.

FrontTWSAfter the consolidation in November 2009, the taxpayers approved a million referendum to construct an addition to Trevor Grade School which will enable all the District’s students to be housed on the Trevor site. State Superintendent Tony Evers even called to commend the District for passage of the referendum in a tough economic time. He felt this reflected well on our residents and their commitment to the children. The 65,000 square foot addition will house the primary students, a new gym, computer lab, library, art rooms, and office space.

Contruction of the new addtion began in August 2010 and was completed in August 2011. The school was once again renamed and became Trevor-Wilmot School. The new school was opened on Friday, August 26, 2011 at 5:45 pm with a dedication ceremony and tours of the new school.

name: KIDS CLUB SUMMER DAYCAMP EVANSVILLE
details:
“Kid’s Club” began in 1993 as a family childcare site AKA; Country Home Family Daycare in the home of the owner, Lisa Nyman. She provided care for 8 children daily from 7 AM till 5:30 PM Monday – Friday.

Our program first expanded into school age care in 1997 by adding the first “Kid’s Club” Before & after School Program, which was named Footville Before & After School Program and held in the Footville elementary school at 121 Janesville Street in Footville, WI. This program cared for children of the Parkview School District and is still in existence today and is owned & operated by Dawn Wells.

The first Belleville site was added in the fall of 2000 when a survey determined that several children were in need of some type of after school care. “Kid’s Club” After School Program / Elem opened in the Belleville Elementary School at 237 Pearl Street, Belleville, WI on September 1st, 2000. This program cared for children, from both the Intermediate & elementary schools, after school until 5:30 PM nightly, as well as additional school days off. “Kid’s Club” received a $25,000.00 grant to start the program from the Department of Workforce and Development. After an increase in enrolment at this site an additional after school program was added and was called “Kid’s Club” After School Program / Int and opened at the Belleville Intermediate School (in the basement / old art room) at 101 South Grant Street in Belleville, WI in September of 2003. Both after school sites currently care for 20-25 children nightly and are still in operation today.

After several years of providing after school care in Belleville the first summer program began on June 11th, 2004 in the Belleville Jr. High School at 625 West Church Street in Belleville, WI. The “Kid’s Club” Summer Day Camp / Belleville enrolled 8 children the first year, and in 2005 enrollment jumped to 32 children daily, and in 2006 enrollment reached 50 children, where it remains today.

The “Kid’s Club” Summer Day Camp / Evansville opened in the Evansville Intermediate School at 340 Fair Street on June 10th, 2012. The Enrollment during the summer of 2012 was 8 children and since has grown to 20 children for the summer of 2013. This program is still in operation today and cares for school age children during the summer months only.

The most recent expansion for “Kid’s Club” Learning Centers Inc. will take place on May 1st, 2013 when it will open “Kid’s Club” Childcare Center at 420 West Highway 11 in Footville, WI. This expansion was brought about since the recent closure of two group centers in the Footville area which opened up a significant need for this type of center in the Footville area. This site will care for infants – school age children 6 AM-6 PM Monday – Friday. It will be open year round.

The staff of the “Kid’s Club” Learning Centers Inc. are excited about what lies ahead for our program. We offer a structured, educational based program with highly educated teachers. We feel that offering a high quality program will benefit the children in our care and since the YoungStar Program was established in 2010 we have made “quality programming” our main goal!!!

Grantosa’s mission is to provide quality education that will increase the knowledge of all students. At Grantosa, our goal is to have students work hard and get smart. We want our students to have the best educational opportunities that we can offer. Most of our staff are lifelong learners. They are committed to continuing enhancing education by  taking classes to learn the latest strategies and techniques available to help prepare our youth for a competing market. We believe that it does take a village to raise and educate a child. We invite all families to come and be a part of a great team! Feel free to contact us at 414-393-4400.

Grantosa Drive School has two technology labs that enable students to have access to educational programs such as Think Central, Raz-Kids, and SpellingConncections.com. All Milwaukee Public School Students have free internet access. The MPS website has secure links that students may use to gather information needed. With technology integrated into the curriculum, students have the opportunity to become familiar with applying technological skills into their education. This is a way of empowering the students to become critical thinkers in today’s society.

name: Academy Of Performing Arts - Oak Creek Franklin
details:
As The Academy continues to grow, we reflect on our company core values to help guide our business to preserve what has always been important to us as a company. These are The Academy’s ten core values:

BUILD A SIMPLE SYSTEM FOR THE FUTURE
Look for the simplest and smartest way to get a result, and then leave a written record of what you have done so others can learn from you.
CONSERVATIVE MINDED
Value the conservative views of our community and be a role model of that mindset.
BE TEACHABLE
Look for and implement the best practices. Be receptive to learning from staff observations, training materials and training classes. Achieve YOUR next level of greatness.
BE OBSERVANT
Be aware of how The Academy looks, sounds, smells and feels at any given moment. Do what you can to ensure we are ready for our newest, longest, and best customer to walk in the door.
BE INNOVATIVE
The Academy is ALWAYS striving to improve. Give your creative ideas freely to help improve the overall employee and customer experience. Always growing!
DELIVER WOW
Give customers of all ages a WOW experience every time through preparation of lesson plans, asking for help when needed, giving prompt and accurate information and creating a safe and caring environment.
DELIVER POSITIVE ENERGY
Bring your positive energy to students, customers and other employees. Answer with more “yes” than “no”, give more compliments than corrections, have more positive suggestions than criticism and show that you value each person.
BE RESPONSIBLE
Take ownership of the work you do and make it your best work. Know when to ask for help. When you make a mistake, go above and beyond to correct it.
BE HONEST
We only make promises we can keep, and we always keep those promises; customer can count on our staff
making recommendations that they really need. We are honest with our customers, even if it means that honesty will cost us money. We act with integrity at all times.
MAKE THE CHANGE HAPPEN
Actions speak louder than words. Jump in and get it done now, regardless of the obstacles.

name: Oconto Falls Public School District
details:
Welcome to Oconto Falls High School, home of the Panthers!  From our storied beginnings in 1904 when the first class to graduate walked across the graduation stage, Oconto Falls High School has positioned itself as one of the leaders in this area of the state.  We have a lot for which to be proud and we welcome friends and families to join our long tradition of excellence. 

Oconto Falls serves approximately 520 students and is located just north of historic Green Bay...Titletown USA!  Our staff of almost 75 people is committed to serving the varied needs that our students and families bring to the school.  Recognized locally and across the state, our faculty boast Kohl Fellows, Wisconsin Teachers of the Year, National Board Certifications, and most importantly 55 teachers who are dedicated to their students success, today and into the future.

Oconto Falls offers many opportunities to help make your high school years the best that they can be.  I strongly recommend that everyone get involved in one or more of the activities that we offer.  Whether the immediate focus is academics, athletics, co-curriculars, or the fine arts, Oconto Falls High School has the programming to help you open new doors, enable you to meet new people, and to reveal to you all the possibilities on which you can grow and mature.  With your ideas, enthusiasm and participation we can continue our tradition of excellence and help ensure that you will have a great school year.

name: Osceola School District Kid's Klub
details:
The Kids' Klub program is a before and after school child care service. Your child will be engaged in a variety of activities on the playground, in their clubroom and school gym. Field trips, swimming & special presentations will be included in this program during the month of June and early release days.

Note: This service does not operate during Thanksgiving, Christmas, Easter or summer (July or August) vacation. If school is canceled due to a winter weather, the program will not operate on that day either. However, we are in operation on days in which school has an early dismissal due to bad weather. On days with two hour late starts, Kids Klub opens two hours late. (Kids Klub is open 8:00-10:15)

The program fees are $2.75 per hour/per child with a $15.00 annual family registration fee.  There is a late pick-up fee of $10.00 per 15-minute.  Breakfast is available before school and is charged to your child’s regular breakfast/lunch account. Breakfast is $1.00. A snack is given after school and is included in the fee.

This program is eligible to receive reimbursement through the Department of Human Services, Private Industry Council, Vocational Rehabilitation, etc. for services provided. For more information contact your case manager or direct inquiries to the Director of Kids' Klub @ 294-3457 ext. 296.

name: Kids Club Childcare Center
details:
“Kid’s Club” began in 1993 as a family childcare site AKA; Country Home Family Daycare in the home of the owner, Lisa Nyman. She provided care for 8 children daily from 7 AM till 5:30 PM Monday – Friday.

Our program first expanded into school age care in 1997 by adding the first “Kid’s Club” Before & after School Program, which was named Footville Before & After School Program and held in the Footville elementary school at 121 Janesville Street in Footville, WI. This program cared for children of the Parkview School District and is still in existence today and is owned & operated by Dawn Wells.

The first Belleville site was added in the fall of 2000 when a survey determined that several children were in need of some type of after school care. “Kid’s Club” After School Program / Elem opened in the Belleville Elementary School at 237 Pearl Street, Belleville, WI on September 1st, 2000. This program cared for children, from both the Intermediate & elementary schools, after school until 5:30 PM nightly, as well as additional school days off. “Kid’s Club” received a $25,000.00 grant to start the program from the Department of Workforce and Development. After an increase in enrolment at this site an additional after school program was added and was called “Kid’s Club” After School Program / Int and opened at the Belleville Intermediate School (in the basement / old art room) at 101 South Grant Street in Belleville, WI in September of 2003. Both after school sites currently care for 20-25 children nightly and are still in operation today.

After several years of providing after school care in Belleville the first summer program began on June 11th, 2004 in the Belleville Jr. High School at 625 West Church Street in Belleville, WI. The “Kid’s Club” Summer Day Camp / Belleville enrolled 8 children the first year, and in 2005 enrollment jumped to 32 children daily, and in 2006 enrollment reached 50 children, where it remains today.

The “Kid’s Club” Summer Day Camp / Evansville opened in the Evansville Intermediate School at 340 Fair Street on June 10th, 2012. The Enrollment during the summer of 2012 was 8 children and since has grown to 20 children for the summer of 2013. This program is still in operation today and cares for school age children during the summer months only.

The most recent expansion for “Kid’s Club” Learning Centers Inc. will take place on May 1st, 2013 when it will open “Kid’s Club” Childcare Center at 420 West Highway 11 in Footville, WI. This expansion was brought about since the recent closure of two group centers in the Footville area which opened up a significant need for this type of center in the Footville area. This site will care for infants – school age children 6 AM-6 PM Monday – Friday. It will be open year round.

The staff of the “Kid’s Club” Learning Centers Inc. are excited about what lies ahead for our program. We offer a structured, educational based program with highly educated teachers. We feel that offering a high quality program will benefit the children in our care and since the YoungStar Program was established in 2010 we have made “quality programming” our main goal!!!

name: Little Beginnings Child Care Center Llc

details:
We would like to start off by welcoming you and your family to our center.  We know that there are a lot of other childcare centers here in the greater Milwaukee area but we want to thank you for choosing us to love, care, educate and nurture your child!
Now we would like to take the time to tell you a little about us.  We have been in business since February 2008.  Our first location was located at76th/Becher.  We out grew the center and relocated to 1627 S. 44 Street in July of 2011.  We also have (2) other locations at 3343 North 35th Street and our newest location at 7330 West Lincoln Avenue that is currently open and accepting enrollment.  The centers are owned and operated by Tangie Cokes with the support of her husband Michael Cokes.
 
We believe that a child's first school experience is vitally important in shaping a child's approach and attitude toward learning.  At Tangie's Just Like Mommy Childcare Center LLC, each child will have the opportunity to be a child.  Each child will have the chance to gain self-esteem, confidence, independence and self-discipline at his/her own individual pace.  Our program has been established to provide a safe, stable and nurturing environment with an academically appropriate education curriculum that prepares them to be successful! 
 
Our professional and caring staff will provide your child with an atmosphere where each individual will know they are special and loved.  We see each child as a unique individual therefore by respecting and responding to each individual needs.  Teachers create a developmentally appropriate learning environment that addresses the needs of your child at each developmental stage. 
 
We teach according to the belief that children are active learner, and learn best through play and hands on opportunities.  Your child will be encouraged to play, discover participate, inquire, experiment,and interact with others.  Families come to us for many reasons, but largely because they recognize that, we will treat their child, just like mommy!

name: Centerpiece Llc
details:
Centerpiece LLC is Green Bay, Wisconsin's first center-based autism treatment program. Centerpiece utilizes Applied Behavioral Analysis, which is a science that develops methods of changing behavior.  In the most basic terms, ABA therapy seeks to change behaviors by extinguishing undesirable behaviors and reinforcing the good behaviors. 

Centerpiece LLC offers clients a unique opportunity to excel and progress through:

    One on one individual teaching time with highly trained and experienced therapists
    Facilitated group activities within the center that allow children the opportunity to immediately practice the skills and behaviors mastered in one on one sessions and interact with their peers.
    Access to therapy tools, toys, and equipment that may not be available to children who receive therapy in home.
    Direct and immediate access to senior level staff and center director when problem behaviors or questions arise.
    Emphasis on providing a wide array of therapy activities to all clients including gross and fine motor activities, structured and unstructured play opportunities, and equipment and activities designed to meet the sensory needs of clients of all ages.

The staff at Centerpiece uses an eclectic approach to therapy, bringing a wide range of ideas, styles and strategies together and harnessing these approaches into a consistent and measurable ABA program.  Centerpiece believes that the child should be at the center of everything we do, not the program!  Our staff have an emphasis on respecting a family's right to choose other complementary therapies (HBOT, special diets, craniosacral, neurofeedback, etc) because we believe that no one therapy or treatment is the answer and it takes an entire toolbox of approaches to get the best results for a child and to change with the child over the years as they grow and progress.  What works for one family may not work for another, and what works for a child may change tomorrow!
